 About this Game

 The Elysium Enigma is a relatively kind game.  It is possible to get
 killed or otherwise arrive at a less than ideal ending, but in such
 cases you can always UNDO.  It should not be possible to put the game
 into an unwinnable state.

 You may well finish the game, or even win the game, with fewer than
 the maximum points (it's possible to win the game with as few as 13
 points, or even 12 on a second or subsequent playthrough).  If you
 arrive at a less than satisfactory ending with a very low score, that
 means that there's a lot of the game you have missed; but if you
 arrive at a winning ending with less than the maximum score that means
 you have seen the essentials but missed out on some optional extras.

 It should be fairly easy to complete this game in the sense of
 reaching some ending, and not too hard to reach a winning ending
 within two hours; achieving the full score of 30 points could prove
 more of a challenge.

 To access in-game hints directly, type HINT (or HINTS).

 Conversation is important in this game, which uses the ASK/TELL
 method.  At any point in a conversation you can use the TOPICS
 commands to list topics it's currently worth asking or telling your
 interlocutor about.  You may find it makes for better gameplay,
 however, if you try asking and telling NPCs about the topics that
 naturally occur to you, rather than treating conversations as a kind
 of speech-maze to be navigated.

 For further details of conversational and other commands, see the "How
 to Play Interactive Fiction" and "Playing this Game" menus.

 To see this menu again type HELP or ABOUT (the commands are equivalent
 in this game).

 This post-comp release of The Elysium Enigma attempts to address some
 of the main criticisms expressed by the comp reviewers, insofar as it
 is possible to do that with relatively minor tweaks that don't affect
 the structure of the game.

 [The End]








